Belarus Devalues Ruble to 4,930 Per Dollar, Interfax Reports

-- B y   A l e x   K u d r y t s k i
-- 
2011-05-23T13:46:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/belarus-devalues-ruble-to-4-930-per-dollar-interfax-reports-1-.html
Belarus’s central bank set its
official ruble exchange rate for tomorrow at 4,930 per dollar,
which amounts to a devaluation of 36 percent, Interfax reported,
citing unidentified people familiar with the decision.  The official dollar-ruble rate for today was set at 3,155
per dollar, according to the central bank’s  website .  Anatoly Drozdov, a spokesman for the central bank, declined
to comment on the report, adding that the regulator plans to
release a statement today on its currency policy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Kudrytski in Minsk, via the Moscow newsroom on
.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
